WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.120
You know, people love RStudio, they love the IDE, they love our pro products, and it's been

00:00:08.120 --> 00:00:14.000
really tough working through the rebrand of RStudio, worrying that R users would get the

00:00:14.000 --> 00:00:17.879
message that, like, we don't believe in R anymore.

00:00:17.879 --> 00:00:19.559
And that's absolutely not the case.

00:00:19.559 --> 00:00:25.360
Like, Posit is not about, like, pivoting from R to Python, it's about broadening and embracing

00:00:25.360 --> 00:00:28.799
the Python community as well as the R community.

00:00:28.799 --> 00:00:35.160
So I think that's my big message for the R community, is, like, we still 100% believe

00:00:35.160 --> 00:00:42.040
in R, I think it is just a fantastic environment for doing interactive data science, and we're

00:00:42.040 --> 00:00:44.160
going to continue to invest in it.

00:00:44.160 --> 00:00:49.959
But what I hope we can bring to the Python ecosystem is some of the sort of, like, beautiful

00:00:49.959 --> 00:00:55.360
end-to-end orchestration that we've provided the R community, where things just work.

00:00:55.759 --> 00:01:00.680
And I think that is, you know, very, you know, broadly what we want with all of our open

00:01:00.680 --> 00:01:06.559
source products, with all of our pro products, that you try something, and it just works

00:01:06.559 --> 00:01:10.239
first time, and it's just such a joyful experience.

